The `$switch` variable does not work in combination with `-file` or when the input is pipeline output.

## Steps to reproduce

`$switch` enumerator works as expected for an array input:

```powershell
    $testData = 1, 2, 3, 4
    $switchIsNull = $true

    $output = switch ($testData) {
        (2) {
            $_
            $switchIsNull = $null -eq $switch
            if ($switch -and $switch.MoveNext()) {
              $switch.Current
            }
        }
    }
    
    PS> $switchIsNull
    False   ## $switch was set
    PS> $output
    2
    3
```

`$switch` enumerator is unset for a file input:

```powershell
    $testData = 1, 2, 3, 4
    $switchIsNull = $true

    Set-Content -LiteralPath 'InputData.txt' -Value $testData
    $output = switch -File InputData.txt {
        (2) {
            $_
            $switchIsNull = $null -eq $switch
            if ($switch -and $switch.MoveNext()) {
                $switch.Current
            }
        }
    }
    Remove-Item InputData.txt

    PS> $switchIsNull
    True  ## $switch was not set
    PS> $output
    2
```

`$switch` enumerator is not retrieved for a list input:

```powershell
    $testData = 1, 2, 3, 4
    $switchIsNull = $true

    $list = [System.Collections.Generic.List[object]]::new()
    $list.AddRange($testData)
    $output = switch ($list) {
        (2) {
            $_
            $switchIsNull = $null -eq $switch
            if ($switch -and $switch.MoveNext()) {
                $switch.Current
            }
        }
    }

    PS> $switchIsNull
    False  ## $switch was set
    PS> $output
    2
    1
```

